!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

professional /prəˈfɛʃənəl/

(professionals) 

1. ADJ Professional means relating to a person's work, especially work that requires special training. 有关职业的 [ADJ n] 

例： His professional career started at Colgate University. 他的职业生涯始于科尔盖特大学。 

2. professionally ADV 职业上地 

例： ...a professionally-qualified architect. …一名职业上合格的建筑师。 

3. ADJ Professional people have jobs that require advanced education or training. 专业的 (人士) [ADJ n] 

例： ...highly qualified professional people like doctors and engineers. …像医生和工程师这样高资历的专业人士。 

4. N-COUNT Professional is also a noun. 专业人士 

例： My father wanted me to become a professional and have more stability. 我父亲希望我成为一名专业人士，有更多稳定性。 

5. ADJ You use professional to describe people who do a particular thing to earn money rather than as a hobby. 职业的 (运动员等) 

例： This has been my worst time for injuries since I started as a professional player. 这是我成为职业球员以来受伤最严重的一次。 

6. N-COUNT Professional is also a noun. 职业人士 

例： He had been a professional since March 

1985. 他自1985年3月以来一直是一名职业人士。 

7. professionally ADV 作为职业地 [ADV after v] 

例： By age 16 he was playing professionally with bands in Greenwich Village. 到16岁时，他已在与格林尼治村的各乐队进行职业演出了。 

8. ADJ Professional sports are played for money rather than as a hobby. 职业的 (运动等) [ADJ n] 

例： ...an art student who had played professional football for a short time. …曾短期踢过职业足球的艺术生。 

9. ADJ If you say something that someone does or produces is professional , you approve of it because you think that it is of a very high standard. 专业水准的 [表赞许] 

例： They run it with a truly professional but personal touch. 他们以真正专业而个性化的方式经营它。 

10. N-COUNT Professional is also a noun. 有专业水准的人 

例： ...a dedicated professional who worked harmoniously with the cast and crew. …一位和全体演职人员合作融洽、敬业、有专业水准的人。 

11. professionally ADV 有专业水准地 [ADV with v] 

例： These tickets have been produced very professionally. 这些标签制作得很专业。

</div>

